From IMDB: Documentary on the birth and emergence of the 
soul music industry in the late 1950's, along the 12-block 
stretch of Chicago's South Michigan Avenue known as "Record Row".

With wonderful narration by Etta James, this is truly a beautiful
documentary. Using classic rare footage, never before seen stills, 
and remembrances by those who were there, this will delight, and
inform those who visit.
